oll, shaking her head in disbelief* It was not too far in her past that she had lost her father's guidance in her life.  More recently, her mentor's life had become forfeit under her hand due to his betrayal.  And now, to hear that the last of those that she had ever considered family was unraveling.<br>
<br>
After countless minutes passed, Natori stood from the worn desk with determination.  The woman had spent the first half of her life learning to be a leader of people, and the second half of her life learning to be a warrior.  It was time to combine these two parts of her heart.<br>
<br>
She sat back down, and began to scribe furiously.  At this time, I am unaware of plans to rebuild after our family is broken.  If there are plans, I stand with our new leaders, if they are worthy.   If there are no plans, then I ask that all those whose hate still burns strongly within to stand with me and continue the work of our Father.<br>
<br>
I know that I am not of as many seasons as many of you, but with your strength, and your experience backing me, we can hold strong through these troubled times.<br>
<br>
As I said in the beginning, if those of more experience than I have already decided to stand forth and lead, I will back them until I am no longer able to lift my sword arm.<br>
<br>
Natori<br>
