<br>
&quot;So, the glorious Harvest is no more. 'tis a pity i do say,&quot; *Marrin takes a deep swig from his mug of mead, the smooth and strangely sweet liquid sliding down his throat*<br>
 &quot;And the child wishes to assume command.&quot; Marrin chuckles<br>
&quot;A quick platinum i do sense, aye...a quick platinum or two.&quot;<br>
<br>
Marrin knew of how the persons of Neriak looked upon him, 'twas not the greatest. But the aged mercenary decided it was a good chance for him to gain status in the Teir'Dal's eyes. His skills were respectable, though all he had of worth was the leather on his back, and the sword of his Father at his side. <br>
<br>
Now, Marrin needed only speak with the Teir'Dal and if they'd accept his assistance in serving the seasoned Valkyrie Natori.<br>
He would enlist in her army and perhaps, gain not only wealth, but faction with her kind.<br>
<br>
Getting up from his table, Marrin walks over to the Inkeep's wife. She was running things while Inkeeper Hunter was away.<br>
