<br>
Suddenly a worn Half-Elf stumbles into the tavern. <br>
&quot;I seek the mercenary Marrin, a letter for him have I&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Get this lad a drink!&quot; Marrin called to Innkeeper Hunter, home from his  journey to Qeynos.&quot; Tossing a few coins to pay for the brew, Marrin spoke to the half elf &quot;I am he which you seek, pray let me see this letter and there might be some gold in it for you.&quot;  The Half-Elf refused the drink, saying he was not allowed to while working. Shrugging, Marrin downed the ale himself. <br>
<br>
Very well, I have been accepted, now I must speak with the Teir'Dal and see if they'd accept my presence in their lands.<br>
<br>
